# Task 5 – Update Set Creation

## Project

**Virtual Agent–Driven SLA Breach Awareness & Justification System**

---

## Objective

This task demonstrates the creation of a dedicated Update Set in ServiceNow to capture all project configurations related to the Virtual Agent–Driven SLA Breach Awareness & Justification System.

---

## Navigation

**System Update Sets → Local Update Sets**

---

## Configuration Details

| Property        | Value                    |
| --------------- | ------------------------ |
| Update Set Name | Virtual Agent for SLA V1 |
| Application     | Global                   |
| State           | In Progress              |

---

## Steps Performed

1. Open **System Update Sets → Local Update Sets**.
2. Click **New**.
3. Enter the Update Set name as **Virtual Agent for SLA V1**.
4. Click **Submit and Make Current**.
5. Verify that the Update Set is active.

---

## Deliverables

* Update Set Configuration
* Active Update Set
* Configuration Screenshots

---

## Expected Outcome

A new Update Set named **Virtual Agent for SLA V1** is created and made current, ensuring that all project customizations are captured for migration and deployment.

---

**Status:** Completed

**Internship:** SmartBridge ServiceNow Administration

**Task:** 5 – Update Set Creation

